                                    <p>You can restrict your search in IxTheo to archival material. If you click on the link labeled “Archivdatenbank ” in a record, you get access to further information in the corresponding archival databases and possibly to the corresponding digital files (if applicable).</p>
                                    <p>To perform a specific search for archived material connected with a person, do the following: Select the “Persons / Corporations” tab above the search field on top of the page and enter the name of the person in the search field. Once you’ve chosen the appropriate person in the list of results, information about this person from various databases will be displayed on the person information page. The section labeled “Archival Collections” gives you a direct access to references of archived material and other manuscript sources, e.g. letters or personal archives. More information on person information pages is available at <a href="<?=$this->url('content-page', ['page' => 'AuthorityPages']) ?>">Person Information Pages</a>.</p>
                                    <p>You can get an overview of all archived material currently referenced in IxTheo with <a href="<?=$this->url('search-results', [], ['query' => ['lookfor' => '','type'=>'AllFields','filter' => 'format:"Archived Material"']]); ?>">this search query</a>.</p>
