                                    <p>In IxTheo, you can filter your search so that it finds only personal archives (which the person has deposited in a library or public archive). This allows you to determine the archive or the library in which the personal archives of a person are kept and the size of those collections.</p>
                                    <p>There are two different ways to find  personal archives: After a search query, you can select the “Personal archives” option in the “Format” facet. Alternatively, you can select the “Persons / Corporations” tab above the search field and enter the name of the person in the search field. In the section labeled “Archival Collections”, personal papers are also listed. More information on person information pages is available at <a href="<?=$this->url('content-page', ['page' =>'AuthorityPages']) ?>">Person Information Pages</a>.</p>
                                    <p>You can get an overview of all personal archives currently referenced in IxTheo with <a href="<?=$this->url('search-results', [], ['query' => ['lookfor' => '','type'=>'AllFields','filter' => 'format:"Literary Remains"']]); ?>">this search query</a>.</p>
